{
  "text": "Different energy storage units in an energy storage system are responsible for high-frequency or low-frequency power fluctuations generated by renewable energy [CITATION_1] . Combined with the characteristics of the two types of energy storage units, the smooth control strategy can use supercapacitor to suppress high-frequency part of the fluctuations in ref P , and batteries to stabilize the low-frequency part of ref P . When the output power of the renewable energy fluctuates greatly, the DC bus power of the microgrid will not fluctuate greatly, and the microgrid can operate reliably. The principle of filter smoothing control strategy for hybrid energy storage is shown in Figure 2 . the power fluctuations of the battery and supercapacitor in the HESS is established as in Equations (1) and (2) ",
  "citation_candidates": [
